ts a reaction you would otherwise propose, follow the research.\n", "raw_response": "{\n  \"target_molecule\": \"Valine\",\n  \"overall_strategy\": \"This network follows the literature-guided evidence bundle for prebiotic valine synthesis and fate. It centers on four hub intermediates/feedstocks that connect atmospheric discharge, Strecker chemistry, inferred branched-ketoacid chemistry, and downstream prebiotic assembly/fate: isobutyraldehyde, valine aminonitrile, 2-ketoisovalerate, and valine. The strongest quantitative support comes from spark-discharge routes using isobutane or methane feeds under Ring & Miller (1984) conditions, with isobutyraldehyde as the mechanistic bridge to Strecker chemistry. Additional literature-supported but non-yield-backed routes include direct Strecker formation/hydrolysis, shock chemistry, VUV ice photochemistry, and inferred alpha-ketoacid amination. Surface and biochemical steps are added only where necessary to connect known literature routes into a single connected bipartite graph and to represent adsorption, oligomerization, and degradation constraints documented in the research bundle.\",\n  \"molecules\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"mol_001\",\n      \"formula\": \"C4H10\",\n      \"iupac_name\": \"2-methylpropane\",\n      \"common_name\": \"isobutane\",\n      \"inchi\": \"InChI=1S/C4H10/c1-4(2)3/h4H,1-3H3\",\n      \"role\": \"starting\",\n      \"environment_formed\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"mol_002\",\n      \"formula\": \"CH4\",\n      \"iupac_name\": \"methane\",\n      \"common_name\": \"methane\",\n      \"inchi\": \"InChI=1S/CH4/h1H4\",\n      \"role\": \"starting\",\n      \"environment_formed\": \"Hydrothermal\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"mol_003\",\n      \"formula\": \"N2\",\n      \"iupac_name\": \"dinitrogen\",\n      \"common_name\": \"nitrogen\",\n      \"inchi\": \"InChI=1S/N2/c1-2\",\n      \"role\": \"starting\",\n      \"environment_formed\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"mol_004